<span id="freeTextContainer14815583316912498699">A clever book. Written like a serial, each chapter adds time, complexity, characters and depth to the story. The first chapter is quite slow, but the book picks up speed as the history and connections between Ryo and Yukiho is revealed and the old policeman Sasagaki attempts to obtain closure. <br/>There is also subtlety in what the author reveals and the choice of information given to the reader.<br/>There is also a sub-history of 20 years of Japan from the 1960s, baseball, pop culture and the early days</span>
